comments.body:
I'm working on a eutester test along these lines:

{code:python}
from eucaops import Eucaops

failed = False

admin = Eucaops(credpath="/tmp/admin")
nonadmin = Eucaops(credpath="/tmp/andy")
zones = admin.ec2.get_all_zones()
if not len(zones):
  failed = True
zone = zones[0]

# Create a volume and snapshot as admin
admin_vol = admin.create_volume(zone.name)
admin_snap = admin.create_snapshot(admin_vol.id)

# Create a volume and snapshot as nonadmin
nonadmin_vol = nonadmin.create_volume(zone.name)
nonadmin_snap = nonadmin.create_snapshot(nonadmin_vol.id)

# This tests the fix to EUCA-3650
if not admin.delete_snapshot(nonadmin_snap):
  failed = True
if not admin.delete_volume(nonadmin_vol):
  failed True

# This tests for regression in delete permissions
try:
  nonadmin.delete_volume(admin_vol)
except EC2ResponseError, e:
  if e.status != 406:
    failed = True

try:
  nonadmin.delete_snapshot(admin_snap)
except EC2ResponseError, e:
  if e.status != 406:
    failed = True
{code}

but I ran into an issue where eutester's high-level functions don't execute as the correct user, so I'm going to suggest a fix to eutester to better support this scenario.  Then I'll finish turning this snippet into a real test case.
